Description:
UImageDisplay is a module to display UImage content in window.
It uses Highgui from OpenCV to manage graphical interface.
This module covers functionality of Image widget from Gostai Lab,
but I hope it consumes less resources.


Requirement:
 - Urbi SDK
 - OpenCV
 - Boost libraries
UImageDsiplay was tested with Urbi SDK 2.7.4, OpenCV 2.3.1 and Boost 1.42.

Module functions:
UImageDisplay.new(string arg1) - constructor, create new window with name `arg1';
UImageDisplay.show(UImage image) - show `image' in window;
UImageDisplay.windowName() - get name of window;

How to use in urbiscript:
loadModule("uimagedisplay");
var u = UImageDisplay.new("Window 1");
var image = // get image from some source
u.show(image);


